│ stop({"edit_points": [[3496, 3500,                                                     │
│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1.             │
│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe transformation in foldBitCeil removes a guarding select  │
│ and synthesizes a new shift count based on the ctlz result. In the source IR, the ctlz │
│ call carries a range metadata !range [1, 33), which makes any actual value that falls  │
│ outside that range poison upon use. For %x = -1, ctlz(%x,false) = 0, which violates    │
│ the metadata range and becomes poison. In the original code, the poison-tainted value  │
│ only flows through the 'true' arm of the select, and the condition chooses the 'false' │
│ arm (constant 1), thus avoiding poison. The transformation eliminates the select and   │
│ unconditionally uses the ctlz-derived value, making the resulting program more         │
│ poisonous. Alive2 confirms this difference.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n- The first    │
│ transform point is foldBitCeil. It rewrites the select to:\n  %1 = sub nsw i32 0,      │
│ %ctlz\n  %2 = and i32 %1, 31\n  %sel = shl nuw i32 1, %2\n- The ctlz call retains the  │
│ range(i32 1, 33) metadata.\n- With x = -1: ctlz = 0; !range says it must be in [1,33), │
│ so using ctlz is poison. The transformed code uses ctlz unconditionally via            │
│ neg/and/shl, producing poison. The source would have selected 1, avoiding              │
│ poison.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nfoldBitCeil only considers arithmetic properties   │
│ and the NUW dropping for the add feeding the pattern, but it does not acknowledge      │
│ poison-generating metadata on the ctlz result. Range metadata is a semantic constraint │
│ that can make a value poison at its use if it is outside the annotated bounds. By      │
│ removing the select guard, foldBitCeil must either prove the ctlz value cannot violate │
│ the annotated range or prevent metadata from propagating poison unexpectedly. As it    │
│ stands, it keeps the range metadata on the ctlz result and then unconditionally uses   │
│ it, which can increase poison propagation and thus breaks correctness.\n\n4. Proposed  │
│ Edit Point(s):\n- File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp\n-       │
│ Location: in foldBitCeil, immediately after handling ShouldDropNUW, before building    │
