│ metadata !range [1, 33), which makes any actual value that falls outside that range    │
│ poison upon use. For %x = -1, ctlz(%x,false) = 0, which violates the metadata range    │
│ and becomes poison. In the original code, the poison-tainted value only flows through  │
│ the 'true' arm of the select, and the condition chooses the 'false' arm (constant 1),  │
│ thus avoiding poison. The transformation eliminates the select and unconditionally     │
│ uses the ctlz-derived value, making the resulting program more poisonous. Alive2       │
│ confirms this difference.                                                              │
