╭─ Assistant [MainThread@707693] ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ I implemented a minimal fix in InstCombine’s foldBitCeil that drops MD_range metadata  │
│ from the ctlz intrinsic result when the guarded select is removed, preventing          │
│ increased poison propagation.                                                          │
│                                                                                        │
│ Change summary:                                                                        │
│ - Location: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                      │
│ - In foldBitCeil, after handling ShouldDropNUW, we now clear MD_range on the ctlz      │
│ call:                                                                                  │
│   if (auto *CtlzI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Ctlz))                                       │
│     CtlzI->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range, nullptr);                                │
│                                                                                        │
│ Rationale:                                                                             │
│ - The original select guards the use of the ctlz result that had range metadata.       │
│ Removing the guard and unconditionally using the ctlz result can make the program more │
│ poisonous if the range metadata is violated (e.g., ctlz(-1,false) = 0, which is        │
│ outside the annotated range [1,33) and thus poison). Clearing MD_range restores        │
│ semantic equivalence.                                                                  │
│                                                                                        │
│ If you still see the range metadata present in the transformed IR for the test, please │
│ ensure that foldBitCeil is the transformation actually applied and that the variable   │
│ “Ctlz” in this context is the call instruction to llvm.ctlz. If the matcher feeds a    │
│ different node, we may also need to explicitly cast and clear metadata using           │
│ cast<Instruction>(Ctlz) rather than CallInst, which the patch currently does.          │
